HEADWORD: Ethyl
<hw>Eth"yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ether</ets> +
<ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A monatomic, hydrocarbon
radical, <chform>C2H5</chform> of the paraffin series, forming the
essential radical of ethane, and of common alcohol and ether.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ethyl aldehyde</b></col>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <cd>See
